{
  "text": "Formulary. An independent home infusion provider does not have to abide by a formulary; drugs are dispensed according to the orders of the physicians in its service area. A hospital-or health-system-based infusion pharmacy may have to abide by the same formulary restrictions as the rest of the hospital or health system. The home infusion pharmacist should have a mechanism for providing input to the formulary committee. [CITATION_1] The pharmacy should have access to specialty medications distributed through closed network systems when needed to support consistent delivery of patient care and medication reconciliation.",
